all|{{nowrap|(Born in {{Flagicon image|Flag of the Kingdom of Lombardy\u2013Venetia.svg}} [[Kingdom of Lombardy\u2013Venetia]])}}}}\n| \"[For his work as a] key leader of the Italian peace movement\"<ref name=\"Lundestad\"/><ref name=\"N1907\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1907/index.html |title=The Nobel Peace Prize 1907 |publisher=Nobel Foundation |accessdate=2011-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111006050412/http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1907/index.html |archive-date=2011-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[File:Louis Renault jurist.gif|75px]]\n| [[Louis Renault (jurist)|Louis Renault]]\n| data-sort-value=\"France\"| {{flagdeco|France|1794}} [[French Third Republic|France]]\n| \"[For his work as a] leading French international jurist and a member of the [[Permanent Court of Arbitration]] at The Hague\"<ref name=\"Lundestad\"/><ref name=\"N1907\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1908\n| [[File:KParnoldson.jpg|75px]]\n| [[Klas Pontus Arnoldson]]\n| {{flag|Sweden}}\n| \"[For his work as] founder of the [[Swedish Peace and Arbitration Society|Swedish Peace and Arbitration League]]\"<ref name=\"Lundestad\"/><ref name=\"N1908\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1908/index.html |title=The Nobel Peace Prize 1908 |publisher=Nobel Foundation |accessdate=2011-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111006045759/http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1908/index.html |archive-date=2011-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Fredrik Bajer nobel.jpg|75px]]\n| [[Fredrik Bajer]]\n| {{flag|Denmark}}\n| \"[For being] the foremost peace advocate in Scandinavia, combining work in the [[Inter-Parliamentary Union]] with being the first president of the [[International Peace Bureau]]\"<ref name=\"Lundestad\"/><ref name=\"N1908\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1909\n| [[File:Beernaert.gif|75px]]\n| [[Auguste Beernaert]]\n| {{flag|Belgium}}<br> {{s