alue=\"France\"| {{flagdeco|France|1794}} [[French Third Republic|France]]\n| \"[For his participation] in both the [[Hague Conventions of 1899 and 1907|Hague Conferences of 1899 and 1907]]\" and for his work towards \"what became the [[League of Nations|League]] to such an extent that he was frequently called its 'spiritual father'\"<ref name=\"Lundestad\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1920/index.html |title=The Nobel Peace Prize 1920 |publisher=Nobel Foundation |accessdate=2011-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111006045134/http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1920/index.html |archive-date=2011-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1921\n| [[File:Hjalmar branting stor bild.jpg|75px]]\n| [[Hjalmar Branting]]\n| {{flag|Sweden}}\n| \"[F]or his work in the [[League of Nations]]\"<ref name=\"Lundestad\"/><ref name=\"N1921\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1921/index.html |title=The Nobel Peace Prize 1921 |publisher=Nobel Foundation |accessdate=2011-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111006045608/http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1921/index.html |archive-date=2011-10-06 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Christian Lous Lange.jpg|75px]]\n| [[Christian Lous Lange|Christian Lange]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{flag|Norway}}\n| \"[For his work as] the first secretary of the Norwegian Nobel Committee\" and \"the secretary-general of the [[Inter-Parliamentary Union]]\"<ref name=\"Lundestad\"/><ref name=\"N1921\"/>\n|-\n| 1922\n| [[File:Fridtjof Nansen LOC 03377u-3.jpg|75px]]\n| [[Fridtjof Nansen]]\n| \"[For] his work in aiding the millions in Russia [[Russian famine of 1921|struggling against famine]]\" and \"his work for the [[Population exchange between Greece and Turkey|refugees in Asia Minor and Thrace]]\"<ref>{{cite web |first=Fredrik |last=Stang |authorlink=Fredrik Stang |url=https://www.nobelprize.org/